  <para style="p">
    <verse number="35" style="v" sid="2CH 20:35" />¶ And <char style="w" strong="H0310">after</char> this did <char style="w" strong="H3092">Jehoshaphat</char> <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3063">Judah</char> <char style="w" strong="H2266">join</char> himself with <char style="w" strong="H0274">Ahaziah</char> <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char>, who <char style="w" strong="H6213">did</char> very <char style="w" strong="H7561">wickedly</char>: <verse eid="2CH 20:35" /><verse number="36" style="v" sid="2CH 20:36" />And he <char style="w" strong="H2266">joined</char> himself with him to <char style="w" strong="H6213">make</char> <char style="w" strong="H0591">ships</char> to <char style="w" strong="H3212">go</char> to <char style="w" strong="H8659">Tarshish</char>: and they <char style="w" strong="H6213">made</char> the <char style="w" strong="H0591">ships</char> in <char style="w" strong="H6100">Ezion-geber</char>. <verse eid="2CH 20:36" /><verse number="37" style="v" sid="2CH 20:37" />Then <char style="w" strong="H0461">Eliezer</char> the <char style="w" strong="H1121">son</char> of <char style="w" strong="H1735">Dodavah</char> of <char style="w" strong="H4762">Mareshah</char> <char style="w" strong="H5012">prophesied</char> against <char style="w" strong="H3092">Jehoshaphat</char>, <char style="w" strong="H0559">saying</char>, Because thou hast <char style="w" strong="H2266">joined</char> thyself with <char style="w" strong="H0274">Ahaziah</char>, the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> hath <char style="w" strong="H6555">broken</char> thy <char style="w" strong="H4639">works</char>. And the <char style="w" strong="H0591">ships</char> were <char style="w" strong="H7665">broken</char>, that they were not <char style="w" strong="H6113">able</char> to <char style="w" strong="H3212">go</char> to <char style="w" strong="H8659">Tarshish</char>.<ve