e="w" strong="H1004">temple</char>, along by the <char style="w" strong="H4196">altar</char> and the <char style="w" strong="H1004">temple</char>, by the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char> round <char style="w" strong="H5439">about</char>.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">23.10 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">side: Heb. shoulder</char></note><note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">23.10 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">temple: Heb. house</char></note> <verse eid="2CH 23:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="2CH 23:11" />Then they brought <char style="w" strong="H3318">out</char> the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king’s</char> <char style="w" strong="H1121">son</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H5414">put</char> upon him the <char style="w" strong="H5145">crown</char>, and <char style="add">gave him</char> the <char style="w" strong="H5715">testimony</char>, and made him <char style="w" strong="H4427">king</char>. And <char style="w" strong="H3077">Jehoiada</char> and his <char style="w" strong="H1121">sons</char> <char style="w" strong="H4886">anointed</char> him, and <char style="w" strong="H0559">said</char>, God <char style="w" strong="H2421">save</char> the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char>.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">23.11 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">God…: Heb. Let the king live</char></note><verse eid="2CH 23:11" /></para>
  <para style="p">
