    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="2CH 30:1" />And <char style="w" strong="H3169">Hezekiah</char> <char style="w" strong="H7971">sent</char> to all <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char> and <char style="w" strong="H3063">Judah</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H3789">wrote</char> <char style="w" strong="H0107">letters</char> also to <char style="w" strong="H0669">Ephraim</char> and <char style="w" strong="H4519">Manasseh</char>, that they should <char style="w" strong="H0935">come</char> to the <char style="w" strong="H1004">house</char> of the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> at <char style="w" strong="H3389">Jerusalem</char>, to <char style="w" strong="H6213">keep</char> the <char style="w" strong="H6453">passover</char> unto the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> <char style="w" strong="H0430">God</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char>. <verse eid="2CH 30:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="2CH 30:2" />For the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char> had taken <char style="w" strong="H3289">counsel</char>, and his <char style="w" strong="H8269">princes</char>, and all the <char style="w" strong="H6951">congregation</char> in <char style="w" strong="H3389">Jerusalem</char>, to <char style="w" strong="H6213">keep</char> the <char style="w" strong="H6453">passover</char> in the <char style="w" strong="H8145">second</char> <char style="w" strong="H2320">month</char>. <verse eid="2CH 30:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="2CH 30:3" />For they <char style="w" strong="H3201">could</char> not <char style="w" strong="H6213">keep</char> it at that <char style="w" strong="H6256">time</char>, because the <char style="w" strong="H3548">priests</char> had not <char style="w" strong="H6942">sanctified</char> themselves <char style="w" strong="H4078">sufficiently</char>, neither had the <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char> gathered themselves <char style="w" strong="H0622">